To identify a contradiction between Moe's testimony and the evidence, we can focus on whether the silk hat was present with the defendant, Max, during the entire time he was supposedly at the scene of the crime. Moe's particular statement "He was wearing it the entire time that he was on the scene" (Testimony 3) is critical. 

Looking back at the evidence, the Silk Hat (Evidence 3) was found at the crime scene. If Max had been wearing it the entire time as Moe testified, it wouldn't have been found separately at the crime scene. This discrepancy suggests that Moe could not have seen Max with the silk hat on his head the entire time, contradicting his specific assertion.

