The evidence "DeMasque's Calling Card" and the testimony "I knew it was an extremely valuable treasure, so I sent my card 10 days beforehand." contradict each other.

Explanation: According to the provided information, the calling card was sent by Mask☆DeMasque to announce his intention to steal the Sacred Urn from the Treasures of Kurain exhibit. Luke Atmey claims in his testimony that he sent the calling card because he knew the urn was an extremely valuable treasure. However, the calling card specifically mentions that it will go after "the most priceless work of art on display," which indicates an intention to shift suspicion. Moreover, the card predates when the urn was fixed to read "AMI" as opposed to the "I AM" seen during the exhibit. Atmey's statement indicates premeditated orchestration in setting up a theft heist.

